00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:41,080
OK. Alrighty, then

233
00:21:44,390 --> 00:21:46,880
No! No more calls for Lisa!

234
00:21:47,930 --> 00:21:50,800
- Hey, Lise, it's me.

235
00:21:50,890 --> 00:21:55,110
Call me when you wake up. Is there any way
you could baby-sit for us on Friday?

236
00:21:55,190 --> 00:21:58,030
I did! I told him!

237
00:22:00,530 --> 00:22:02,410
What's your name?

238
00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:04,200
OK.

239
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:06,530
..but then I gotta hear about it for a month.

240
00:22:06,620 --> 00:22:09,790
I called everyone who could possibly do it
and no one's free.

241
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:12,710
Call Vanessa.

242
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,800
I said, call Vanessa and ask her about Debbie.

243
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:18,710
Anyway, call me back. Bye.

244
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:21,630
Debbie? That's the girl
who baby-sits for them?

245
00:22:21,710 --> 00:22:22,840
Yep.

246
00:22:22,930 --> 00:22:26,260
Oh, great idea. Pray she's free.

247
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:29,430
- How'd you know about Debbie?
- Samantha told me.

248
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:33,470
Hey, Vanessa.
Are you guys going out Friday night?

249
00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:38,720
Hi. I'm Debbie.

250
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,480
Kozak...?

251
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:48,620
Tom Witzky.

252
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:53,990
- Hi, Debbie. I'm Maggie.
- Hi.

253
00:22:54,090 --> 00:22:57,950
Thanks for coming. Jake's asleep already
and he hardly ever wakes up.

254
00:22:58,040 --> 00:23:01,950
A band could play in his room
and he wouldn't hear it!

255
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:06,750
His room's upstairs, kitchen's back there.
Just help yourself if you want anything.

256
00:23:06,850 --> 00:23:09,460
Here, have a seat.
This is the baby monitor.

257
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:13,300
It's on B in his room,
so you should hear everything.

258
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,510
- You wanna watch a movie?
- I got a book.

259
00:23:15,860 --> 00:23:18,430
It shouldn't be later than midnight,
if that's OK.

260
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,610
- Perfect.
- Great. I'll just grab my coat.

261
00:23:21,690 --> 00:23:24,060
Hello!

262
00:23:24,450 --> 00:23:26,190
- Ready?

263
00:23:26,280 --> 00:23:28,070
- Yeah. Just about.
- OK.

264
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:31,900
Hey. Where'd you find that girl Debbie?

265
00:23:31,990 --> 00:23:36,910
Vanessa gave me her number.
Everybody uses her. It's cool.

266
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:40,950
- Another headache?
- Too much caffeine.

267
00:23:41,040 --> 00:23:44,300
OK, let's go.

268
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:47,330
Bye.

269
00:23:53,150 --> 00:23:56,480
I think that Damon kid
is doing a great job and everything...

270
00:23:56,560 --> 00:24:00,510
..and yeah, the kid's got a decent arm,
but high-school football is about...

271
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:05,190
..power, it's about running the goddamn
football - it always has been.

272
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:07,600
What did you play in high school?

273
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:11,560
- Piano, mostly.
- Jesus! Sorry. Here, you want some?

274
00:24:11,660 --> 00:24:16,160
Anyway, Adam...
and I admit that I am biased...

275
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:20,070
..but my kid is having a helluva season
and it's like nobody even notices.

276
00:24:20,170 --> 00:24:22,840
If they gave him the ball,
he could break a thousand yards!

277
00:24:22,930 --> 00:24:25,620
And that's in an eight-game season.
Jesus Christ!

278
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:28,920
Why don't you just lick 'em
when they walk by?

279
00:24:35,770 --> 00:24:40,550
Frank says the average guy carries around
a hard-on two hours out of every day.

280
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:45,350
- Three for him.
- See, now I got a picture of that!

281
00:24:45,450 --> 00:24:49,850
One of these days, she's gonna find
one of my .38s and pop a cap in my ass!

282
00:24:50,150 --> 00:24:54,290
He'll stick it in a bowl of soup
if it's still warm.

283
00:25:03,630 --> 00:25:06,080
Go! Go!

284
00:25:19,930 --> 00:25:23,190
- Are you OK?
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

285
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:30,940
Over a thousand yards,
we're talking college scholarship!

286
00:25:31,030 --> 00:25:34,740
Hey, come on...
The kid can write his own ticket.

287
00:25:34,830 --> 00:25:39,150
And that's good for everybody. It's good
for the whole goddamn neighbourhood.

288
00:25:39,250 --> 00:25:42,030
He's gonna go a helluva lot further
than lever did.

289
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:47,120
Look at the quality of tail he gets. He passed
me in that department when he was 14.

290
00:25:47,210 --> 00:25:50,250
Come on! While we're young?

291
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:20,820
You scared me!

292
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,120
She's downstairs, I think.

293
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:32,290
I don't know.
I haven't seen her yet.

294
00:26:41,010 --> 00:26:42,500
Jake?

295
00:26:46,070 --> 00:26:48,510
- What's the matter?
- Something's wrong.

296
00:26:48,610 --> 00:26:49,850
What?

297
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:01,230
I have a secret to tell you.

298
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:05,200
Promise, promise, promise?

299
00:27:14,350 --> 00:27:17,680
Samantha says it's always dark where she is.

300
00:27:19,140 --> 00:27:21,340
Who did you say?

301
00:27:21,430 --> 00:27:23,260
Samantha.

302
00:27:26,810 --> 00:27:30,150
You... you talked to Samantha?

303
00:27:30,230 --> 00:27:31,720
Yeah!

304
00:27:31,810 --> 00:27:33,650
When?

305
00:27:33,740 --> 00:27:35,810
All the time.

306
00:27:37,950 --> 00:27:41,150
- Where?
- Here. In my house.

307
00:27:41,490 --> 00:27:42,960
That's not true.

308
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:46,070
Go.

309
00:27:46,170 --> 00:27:47,200
Go!

310
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:52,670
- It isn't true.
- I don't tell lies!

311
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:55,000
Samantha was here? Here, in your house?

312
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:57,500
- You're hurting my arm!
- Was she here?

313
00:27:57,590 --> 00:28:01,170
- Let go of me!
- Come on, you're coming with me. Let's go.

314
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:04,650
She's taking him away.

315
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:16,900
Put me down! Put... me... down!

316
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:23,170
Tom!

317
00:28:34,130 --> 00:28:35,790
Jake!

318
00:28:36,260 --> 00:28:38,330
Jake!

319
00:28:39,180 --> 00:28:41,930
Jake!

320
00:28:42,010 --> 00:28:43,930
- What the hell...?
- She took him.

321
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,730
- What?
- The fucking baby-sitter.

322
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:47,440
Oh, my God!

323
00:28:47,520 --> 00:28:50,010
He's not in there.

324
00:28:50,100 --> 00:28:53,730
- Where are you going?
- I don't know!

325
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,680
He's in there.

326
00:29:53,010 --> 00:29:54,460
- Jake!
- Daddy!

327
00:29:54,550 --> 00:29:57,630
- That's him!
- Wait! Where do you think you're going?

328
00:29:57,710 --> 00:30:00,710
Take it easy! Stop! Stop!
Take it easy. Take it easy.

329
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:03,810
- Gimme my kid.
- Tell me where she is! No!

330
00:30:03,890 --> 00:30:06,590
You tell me where she is!
You tell me where she is!

331
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:09,880
- Keep your hands off her!
- Hey! Hey, hey! Everybody shut up!

332
00:30:09,970 --> 00:30:13,470
- Are you OK?
- That girl kidnapped our son.

333
00:30:13,570 --> 00:30:15,850
- Is that your child?
- Ask about Samantha.

334
00:30:15,940 --> 00:30:19,140
I'm asking about the boy,
who doesn't look like he's yours!

335
00:30:19,230 --> 00:30:22,720
- I can explain this.
- I'm not talking to you. I'm talking to her.

336
00:30:22,830 --> 00:30:24,900
- Is that boy your child?
- No.

337
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:27,480
She was baby-sitting for us. We never...

338
00:30:27,580 --> 00:30:30,780
What you've done is a felony.
You can go to jail for this!

339
00:30:30,870 --> 00:30:33,960
- Where were you taking him?
- I wasn't taking him anywhere!

340
00:30:34,050 --> 00:30:37,080
- Then why did ya bring him here?
- I wanna press charges.

341
00:30:37,170 --> 00:30:39,740
She came here because of me.
I'm her mother.

342
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:44,060
- Her mother?
- When are you gonna ask about Samantha?

343
00:30:44,140 --> 00:30:46,920
- Who?
- My oldest daughter. She ran away.

344
00:30:47,010 --> 00:30:50,380
No, she was kidnapped,
and the little boy said he saw her!

345
00:30:50,470 --> 00:30:54,060
We haven't heard from her in a long time.
We filed a police report.

346
00:30:54,150 --> 00:30:57,560
- Nobody returns our phone calls.
- Jake said he talked to her.

347
00:30:57,650 --> 00:31:00,730
He said Samantha is in their house.
Is that her?

348
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:03,660
- Stay away from him.
- Look at the picture.

349
00:31:03,740 --> 00:31:05,620
- Let go of me!
- Look at the picture.

350
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:09,860
- This is ridiculous.
- Will you look at the picture, please?

351
00:31:13,460 --> 00:31:17,750
- I have never seen her before in my life.
- What about you?

352
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:22,120
No. I'm sorry. I've never seen her.

353
00:31:22,210 --> 00:31:26,040
- No... No. No, they're lying!
- You wanna file charges?

354
00:31:26,140 --> 00:31:27,460
- Yes!
- No.

355
00:31:27,550 --> 00:31:31,630
- What?
- Come on, let's just... forget about it.

356
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:34,140
Let's go home.

357
00:31:34,230 --> 00:31:37,350
Are you nuts? What about
the next people she baby-sits for?

358
00:31:37,440 --> 00:31:39,680
It was her. Samantha.

359
00:31:39,770 --> 00:31:44,520
That girl in the picture,
she's the same girl I saw on our couch.

360
00:31:44,620 --> 00:31:49,110
See, why... Why did you ask that girl Debbie
to baby-sit for us? Why her?

361
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:53,750
I couldn't find anybody else.
I was on the phone and Jake said...

362
00:31:56,960 --> 00:32:02,120
Jake? Do you remember the other day
when we were talking in the kitchen?

363
00:32:03,590 --> 00:32:09,290
I was looking for a baby-sitter, remember?
You said Samantha told you about Debbie.

364
00:32:09,390 --> 00:32:11,540
Do you remember that?

365
00:32:13,730 --> 00:32:16,220
Mommy's asking you a question, bud.

366
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:21,340
Is Samantha someone
who talks to you sometimes, Jake?

367
00:32:23,610 --> 00:32:28,480
- Can you remember...
- Don't ask the boy any more questions.

368
00:32:28,570 --> 00:32:30,690
Talk to me.

369
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:36,030
What did you say?

370
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:39,870
Jake. W-what did you say just now?

371
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:43,370
- Nothing.
- Let me hear that voice again.

372
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:46,870
- Come on. Say it again. Use that voice again.
- Tom!

373
00:32:46,970 --> 00:32:49,720
Come... Come on, Jake. Come on.
Use the voice again.

374
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:52,750
- Tom!
- Make the voice again, Jake. You can do it.

375
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:54,640
- Tom, don't!
- How do you...

376
00:32:54,730 --> 00:32:57,260
- Tom, please!
- It's all right! It's all right!

377
00:32:57,350 --> 00:33:00,350
- OK!
- What are you doing? Hey! Hey!

378
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:02,630
I'm talking to him!

379
00:33:03,610 --> 00:33:06,810
- Hey, what's the matter with you?
- What do you think?

380
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:10,600
Well, I'm just trying
to have a conversation with my kid.

381
00:33:10,700 --> 00:33:13,820
A perfectly normal conversation
for a five-year-old

382
00:33:13,910 --> 00:33:16,030
- Don't be afraid of it.
- Why the hell not?

383
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:19,320
I don't know. That's what he told me.

384
00:33:19,410 --> 00:33:21,950
This is where it happened.
This is where I saw her.

385
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:26,590
- You're different. You feel different.
- I leaned back and there she was. She's 18.

386
00:33:26,670 --> 00:33:29,460
- Longish hair. Is that what you saw?
- I wish you...

387
00:33:29,550 --> 00:33:32,080
- Maggie, please!
- God!

388
00:33:32,170 --> 00:33:36,670
Or... or maybe you don't see her?
You just hear her? Is that what it is?

389
00:33:36,770 --> 00:33:40,020
- Tom, stop it!
- I need to find a way to make her come back.

390
00:33:40,100 --> 00:33:43,560
- Maybe if I hang out here long enough...
- I'm talking to you!

391
00:33:43,650 --> 00:33:47,390
..maybe she'll come back. Maybe
you could talk to her. Help me out here.

392
00:33:47,490 --> 00:33:52,030
- Hey, come on! Hey! What's the problem?
- Knock it off!

393
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:58,860
I don't wanna talk about this
because it scares Mommy.

394
00:34:51,750 --> 00:34:53,840
- Turn it up, man.
- What?

395
00:34:53,930 --> 00:34:56,210
Turn it up. Up!

396
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:22,150
Tom is looking especially together today.

397
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:25,450
He grunted a very pleasant greeting
at me, actually.

398
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:29,750
He's becoming sort of monosyllabic.
Nothing wrong with that guy.

399
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:32,950
Nothing a little lithium couldn't cure!

400
00:35:36,550 --> 00:35:39,720
- I'm a jerk. I'm sorry.
- No...

401
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,430
Are you OK?

402
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:46,140
Over there! In the door!

403
00:35:46,230 --> 00:35:49,890
If you live on the base,
your room and board's covered.

404
00:35:49,980 --> 00:35:55,110
- You still gotta get up early.
- I'll retire, make a coupla down payments.

405
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:58,120
When I take off the uniform,
I'm a landlord already.

406
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:00,950
Five years later, I got three houses.

407
00:36:01,030 --> 00:36:03,320
- Hey. Hey, Har.
- How're ya doin'?

408
00:36:03,420 --> 00:36:06,620
Whaddaya know
about that girl Samantha Kozak?

409
00:36:06,710 --> 00:36:09,660
Samantha Kozak. Why do I know that name?

410
00:36:09,750 --> 00:36:13,890
Brownish hair, 16 or 17 years old.
Used to live around here.

411
00:36:13,970 --> 00:36:16,670
- Oh, yeah, yeah. I remember her, I think.
- Let's go.

412
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:19,760
Hey, Kurt! Come here for a second.

413
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:22,330
Like he ever tells me anything, right?

414
00:36:22,430 --> 00:36:25,140
Get over here!

415
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:28,640
Say, you know that Kozak girl?

416
00:36:28,730 --> 00:36:31,730
- Debbie.
- No, no, no, the other one. Samantha.

417
00:36:31,810 --> 00:36:35,480
Oh, you mean the retard.
Yeah, she ran away.

418
00:36:35,570 --> 00:36:38,520
Yeah, that's right. I remember that.
So, what about her?

419
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:42,350
I just been thinking about her a lot.

420
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:46,110
Why?

421
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:49,700
Her sister baby-sat for us.

422
00:36:55,680 --> 00:36:58,430
This is the first time
he's been out in a week.

423
00:36:58,510 --> 00:37:01,210
He hasn't gone to work.
He sleeps 12 hours a night.

424
00:37:01,300 --> 00:37:06,760
He's used up all his sick days. If he doesn't
show up on Monday, they'll dock him.

425
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:11,050
I can't get him more than six feet
from the couch.

426
00:37:11,140 --> 00:37:14,940
- Why?
- That's where she appeared to him.

427
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:19,690
I'm not shocked that
there's another woman.

428
00:37:19,780 --> 00:37:23,570
Of course, the fact that she's dead
gives one pause.

429
00:37:24,620 --> 00:37:27,740
We are talking about a ghost here,
aren't we, Maggie?

430
00:37:27,830 --> 00:37:31,960
She took off... last March.
With a black guy, I think.

431
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:35,050
Hey, Harry.
Did she ever live in our house?

432
00:37:35,130 --> 00:37:39,420
No, no, no. I just... I just bought that one.
You're the first tenants.

433
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:43,970
Tom and Jake, it's like they have
this private club or something.

434
00:37:44,060 --> 00:37:48,720
They sit in the living room and whisper,
and, as soon as I walk in, they both shut up.

435
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:53,730
You know what you need to do? Find a
young priest with smouldering good looks...

436
00:37:53,820 --> 00:37:56,270
..who can guide you through this.

437
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:58,680
I'm kidding, but I'm not.

438
00:37:58,780 --> 00:38:03,990
Look, I give Tom a lotta shit, but the truth is,
you guys are the best couple on earth.

439
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:08,370
This is on you now, Maggie. Get some help.
Find out why this is happening.

440
00:38:08,450 --> 00:38:10,650
There is a reason.

441
00:38:10,750 --> 00:38:15,410
You won't be the first woman who's
had to hold an insane family together.

442
00:38:15,510 --> 00:38:17,950
Tom's not crazy.

443
00:38:18,050 --> 00:38:22,120
Yes he is. But at least
he's getting interesting.

444
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:24,300
Sports flash! Sports flash!

445
00:38:24,390 --> 00:38:26,630
211 yards rushing on Friday night.

446
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:30,210
That's a total of 894 yards,
with two games to go.

447
00:38:30,310 --> 00:38:32,920
The kid needs 106 yards. That's 53 a game.

448
00:38:33,020 --> 00:38:36,520
He could walk through the next two games
and still break a thousand!

449
00:38:36,610 --> 00:38:39,610
- Frank, what about you? Do you know her?
- Who?

450
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:42,860
Tom was asking about that Kozak girl
from over by Baldwin.

451
00:38:42,940 --> 00:38:46,480
- You remember: the one who ran away?
- The retard.

452
00:38:46,580 --> 00:38:48,820
Shut up, Lenny. Don't use that word.

453
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:51,480
- He's just kinda slow.
- What? Retard?

454
00:38:51,580 --> 00:38:54,040
Goddammit, Lenny,
shut your fuckin' pie hole!

455
00:38:54,130 --> 00:38:56,370
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Heads up!

456
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:03,080
- What are you doing?
- Hey, hey, hey!

457
00:39:03,890 --> 00:39:09,500
Somebody's always gotta ruin it.
They can't ever just be nice.

458
00:40:06,870 --> 00:40:09,560
Frank. What are you doing here?

459
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:14,820
They're gonna kill you, Tommy.

460
00:40:16,790 --> 00:40:19,490
You and Maggie both.

461
00:40:34,100 --> 00:40:37,140
Why would you
say something like that, Frank?

462
00:40:37,230 --> 00:40:40,150
This is a decent neighbourhood.

463
00:40:43,490 --> 00:40:46,100
Hey, are you OK?

464
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:49,150
Where's Sheila? Is she at home?

465
00:40:53,030 --> 00:40:55,570
