488
00:43:58,760 --> 00:44:00,840
Help!

489
00:44:06,860 --> 00:44:09,550
Oh, my God! Oh, my God, my baby!

490
00:44:09,650 --> 00:44:12,510
- Hold on. Hold on.
- Let me... Let me go!

491
00:44:12,610 --> 00:44:17,560
- Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
- Is he alive? Is he alive?

492
00:44:17,660 --> 00:44:22,200
Oh, my God, Adam!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

493
00:44:25,290 --> 00:44:28,070
Adam! Adam!

494
00:44:33,290 --> 00:44:36,500
I'm gonna take him for a walk or something.

495
00:44:37,550 --> 00:44:41,130
- Come on, sweetie pie. Let's get your jacket.
- Where are we going?

496
00:44:57,450 --> 00:45:01,770
- Well! Hello, there!
- Well, hello... there.

497
00:45:04,620 --> 00:45:06,700
Listen! Music!

498
00:45:06,790 --> 00:45:08,950
It's beautiful!

499
00:45:11,870 --> 00:45:14,040
Hey! Jake, wait up!

500
00:45:59,920 --> 00:46:05,600
I don't think we're supposed to be here,
sweetie. Come on, let's go. This way.

501
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:16,230
This place is cool!

502
00:46:37,340 --> 00:46:40,450
Come on, honey. Let's go get some lunch.

503
00:46:48,850 --> 00:46:51,090
Mom! What's this thing?

504
00:46:51,180 --> 00:46:55,020
- I don't know. Let me take a look.
- It looks like some kinda stone.

505
00:46:55,110 --> 00:46:58,220
- Either that, or it's a medal.
- Yeah, I think it is.

506
00:46:58,320 --> 00:47:01,430
- ''Served in the...''
- Look. A flag.

507
00:47:04,200 --> 00:47:07,860
- Everything OK?
- It's fine. Just fine.

508
00:47:08,700 --> 00:47:12,150
We're not supposed to be here?

509
00:47:12,240 --> 00:47:16,120
Oh, no. It's fine. Really.

510
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:19,830
OK. See you later.

511
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:22,450
The boy's got the eyes on him, doesn't he?

512
00:47:25,180 --> 00:47:27,380
X-ray.

513
00:47:31,100 --> 00:47:33,800
Not you, though.

514
00:47:34,230 --> 00:47:36,760
Possibly Daddy?

515
00:47:37,820 --> 00:47:40,140
They're not the only ones.

516
00:47:40,230 --> 00:47:44,400
Tell Daddy to come by and see me
a little later tonight.

517
00:47:45,030 --> 00:47:47,730
He might learn a few things.

518
00:47:55,670 --> 00:47:57,740
Bye, Jake.

519
00:48:01,290 --> 00:48:02,840
Bye, Neil.

520
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:11,290
His name is Neil.

521
00:48:43,420 --> 00:48:46,000
Try that, Daddy.

522
00:48:52,430 --> 00:48:54,510
Why do I know that song?

523
00:48:54,600 --> 00:48:56,800
I'll be home right after the movie.

524
00:48:56,900 --> 00:48:59,510
I know it. I know it!

525
00:48:59,600 --> 00:49:01,970
I said, I won't be late.

526
00:49:07,990 --> 00:49:09,150
OK.

527
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:11,850
Bye, Mom. Bye, Maggie.

528
00:49:52,570 --> 00:49:54,820
Oh, hello.

529
00:49:54,910 --> 00:49:58,080
I don't know if I'm in the right place.
I'm looking for Neil.

530
00:49:58,160 --> 00:50:00,450
Excuse me?

531
00:50:00,540 --> 00:50:02,740
I'm sorry...

532
00:50:19,140 --> 00:50:20,880
Shit!

533
00:50:20,980 --> 00:50:24,100
Shit! Shit! Shit! Shit!

534
00:50:40,450 --> 00:50:43,070
I wanna see Neil.

535
00:50:45,670 --> 00:50:48,290
Wait here.

536
00:50:49,340 --> 00:50:51,950
I don't know her.

537
00:50:54,060 --> 00:50:58,550
What are you doing?
I said the boy's father. I said tell him to come.

538
00:50:58,640 --> 00:51:03,630
He'd never do it. He'd kill me if he knew I was
talking to you about this. He's so paranoid.

539
00:51:03,720 --> 00:51:06,980
What's the story, man?
Close the fucking door!

540
00:51:07,070 --> 00:51:10,930
- So are they. I can't let you in.
- Who are they?

541
00:51:11,030 --> 00:51:14,610
Look, man, this ain't no freak show in here!
Close the damn door!

542
00:51:14,700 --> 00:51:17,110
Look, you just gotta get outta here.

543
00:51:17,200 --> 00:51:19,440
My husband is losing his mind.

544
00:51:19,540 --> 00:51:21,860
I don't know why, but I think you do.

545
00:51:21,950 --> 00:51:26,700
You can tell me what you know, but you can't
tell me to go away because I'm not moving.

546
00:51:33,210 --> 00:51:35,750
- How long has he had it?
- Just a few days.

547
00:51:35,850 --> 00:51:38,800
- What happened? A car wreck?
- No.

548
00:51:38,890 --> 00:51:41,090
- A child die?
- No!

549
00:51:41,180 --> 00:51:43,960
- Did he kill someone?
- He was hypnotised.

550
00:51:44,070 --> 00:51:47,600
- Is that what started it?
- It comes and it goes.

551
00:51:47,690 --> 00:51:52,320
Some people have it for five seconds.
Some, their whole lives.

552
00:51:52,400 --> 00:51:55,110
He's a receiver now. Everything's coming in.

553
00:51:55,200 --> 00:51:59,740
He can't stop it. He can't slow it down.
He can't even figure it out.

554
00:51:59,830 --> 00:52:04,740
It's like he's in a tunnel with a flashlight,
but the light only comes on once in a while.

555
00:52:04,840 --> 00:52:08,240
He gets a glimpse of something,
but not enough to know what it is.

556
00:52:08,340 --> 00:52:10,410
Just enough to know it's there.

557
00:52:10,750 --> 00:52:13,030
- Jake, too.
- Your son?

558
00:52:13,290 --> 00:52:15,340
Much better flashlight.

559
00:52:15,850 --> 00:52:20,500
- Does he know what it wants yet?
- What who wants?

560
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:24,390
He saw a ghost, didn't he?
What did it ask him to do?

561
00:52:24,480 --> 00:52:28,100
- She didn't ask anything.
- Maybe he wasn't listening.

562
00:52:28,190 --> 00:52:31,440
She's asked for something,
and now she's waiting...

563
00:52:31,520 --> 00:52:35,440
..getting more and more pissed off
that he's not doing it.

564
00:52:35,530 --> 00:52:39,060
If he doesn't do her thing,
she'll never go away.

565
00:52:45,920 --> 00:52:48,950
Kill her! Kill her! Kill her!

566
00:53:19,570 --> 00:53:22,850
- Absolutely not!
- Oh, please, please, please!

567
00:53:22,950 --> 00:53:28,790
- Five more minutes. Five more minutes.
- No, zero minutes. Oh, this is cool.

568
00:53:28,870 --> 00:53:32,240
- ''The Mummy'' gives you nightmares.
- No fair!

569
00:53:32,330 --> 00:53:35,590
I know. I'm gonna take a bath.
Are you OK for ten minutes?

570
00:53:35,680 --> 00:53:38,080
Whatever!

571
00:53:58,490 --> 00:54:00,560
How do I know this song?

572
00:54:00,650 --> 00:54:04,790
I know I know this song. I know it. I know it.

573
00:54:18,340 --> 00:54:20,910
Freezing!

574
00:54:22,050 --> 00:54:24,340
Round up your weapons, folks!

575
00:54:24,430 --> 00:54:28,010
Charge!

576
00:54:35,150 --> 00:54:38,070
I don't wanna talk right now.

577
00:54:39,740 --> 00:54:41,280
Hey!

578
00:54:53,750 --> 00:54:55,830
No, no...

579
00:55:03,830 --> 00:55:08,660
Tom? I think the pilot blew out
on the water heater again.

580
00:55:08,760 --> 00:55:11,420
Can you go light it for me?

581
00:55:12,670 --> 00:55:14,960
Hello?

582
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:19,310
Or I could go light it.

583
00:55:48,460 --> 00:55:50,090
Thanks, Colonel.

584
00:55:52,500 --> 00:55:55,210
I said no!

585
00:56:10,650 --> 00:56:12,720
Bummer!

586
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:22,080
Hey! That is the most amazing...

587
00:58:20,570 --> 00:58:21,850
Tom?

588
00:58:22,150 --> 00:58:24,830
Tom! Breathe!

589
00:58:26,040 --> 00:58:29,070
What happened?

590
00:58:29,160 --> 00:58:30,650
- She's there.
- What?

591
00:58:30,750 --> 00:58:32,820
She's there.

592
00:58:37,670 --> 00:58:40,250
What?

593
00:58:40,670 --> 00:58:43,450
Oh, my God!

594
00:58:54,740 --> 00:58:59,310
I want you to hypnotise me again.
All this shit - I want it out, I want it gone.

595
00:58:59,400 --> 00:59:03,720
- I want it all to stop. Right now!
- Come right in. I want you to meet Clarita.

596
00:59:03,820 --> 00:59:05,650
Hi. Sorry.

597
00:59:05,750 --> 00:59:07,980
Sorry, I...

598
00:59:08,080 --> 00:59:10,650
Look, do you think that you could...

599
00:59:10,750 --> 00:59:13,150
- Could she...
- Yeah...

600
00:59:27,020 --> 00:59:31,000
I know. I...

601
00:59:32,020 --> 00:59:34,250
Well, gracias.

602
00:59:35,980 --> 00:59:38,930
OK, you gotta... slow down. OK?

603
00:59:39,030 --> 00:59:43,320
You gotta be a little patient with me here
cos I got a confession to make.

604
00:59:43,400 --> 00:59:47,950
Y'see, we... we just smoked this great big
fatty a few minutes before you walked in...

605
00:59:48,040 --> 00:59:52,490
- ..so this is blowing my mind a bit extra.
- Listen to me. Listen to me!

606
00:59:52,580 --> 00:59:58,500
- Yeah? - Whatever...
door you opened in my brain...

607
00:59:58,590 --> 01:00:00,740
..l want you to shut it.

608
01:00:00,840 --> 01:00:02,800
- Now!
- OK.

609
01:00:02,880 --> 01:00:05,090
I'll do it. OK.
I can do that.

610
01:00:05,810 --> 01:00:08,130
Close your eyes.

611
01:00:08,220 --> 01:00:13,970
OK. Just like last time,
I want you to just focus and concentrate.

612
01:00:15,270 --> 01:00:21,220
Listen to the sounds of the room,
listen to the sounds of your breathing.

613
01:00:21,320 --> 01:00:25,110
Look at the back of your eyelids.
Do you see anything there?

614
01:00:25,200 --> 01:00:28,730
- Could you just get to it, please?
- All right. All right.

615
01:00:29,410 --> 01:00:32,900
I want you to pretend
you're back in the movie theatre.

616
01:00:32,990 --> 01:00:35,120
It's very dark...

617
01:00:35,210 --> 01:00:39,840
..and in the whole pitch-black theatre, the
only thing you can see is the white screen.

618
01:00:39,920 --> 01:00:44,410
As you focus on the screen,
you begin to drift closer to it in your chair.

619
01:00:44,500 --> 01:00:49,050
You'll notice that there are letters
on the screen - tall, thick, black letters.

620
01:00:49,140 --> 01:00:52,420
But they're out of focus,
so you begin to drift closer to them.

621
01:00:52,510 --> 01:00:56,090
- Someone's here.
- No, it's empty.

622
01:00:56,730 --> 01:00:58,930
But there's someone else in here.

623
01:00:59,020 --> 01:01:02,510
- No, you're alone in the theatre, Tom.
- No. No, I'm not.

624
01:01:02,610 --> 01:01:07,310
- Your feet and your ankles are relaxed.
- No. Hard to breathe.

625
01:01:07,410 --> 01:01:11,730
Your hands are limp and heavy.
Your... your arms...

626
01:01:11,820 --> 01:01:15,240
- No air! No air!
- Tom, I want you to look at the screen.

627
01:01:15,330 --> 01:01:16,990
Look at the screen.

628
01:01:17,080 --> 01:01:18,910
Hey.

629
01:01:20,580 --> 01:01:23,950
You can read the letters now.
You're right up next to them.

630
01:01:24,580 --> 01:01:26,920
Tom! Look at the screen!

631
01:01:28,430 --> 01:01:30,500
No!

632
01:01:31,640 --> 01:01:35,590
Wow! What... what happened? Are you OK?

633
01:01:35,690 --> 01:01:39,180
You need to sit down. What was happening
there was very next level.

634
01:01:39,270 --> 01:01:42,300
You should have seen your face.
D'you want a beer?

635
01:01:42,400 --> 01:01:44,940
Are you feeling better? What happened?

636
01:01:46,820 --> 01:01:48,890
I'm supposed to dig.

637
01:02:00,170 --> 01:02:02,240
Hi!

638
01:02:08,510 --> 01:02:10,160
Hello?

639
01:02:13,180 --> 01:02:15,720
Anybody home?

640
01:02:18,600 --> 01:02:21,720
Wow! Look what I'm not cleaning up.

641
01:02:34,910 --> 01:02:36,990
Interesting!

642
01:02:54,340 --> 01:02:57,050
OK!

643
01:03:04,730 --> 01:03:08,070
Hi, honey. What you doin'?

644
01:03:08,150 --> 01:03:11,270
Dad said I'm supposed to dig.

645
01:03:16,700 --> 01:03:19,190
Nice

646
01:03:21,540 --> 01:03:23,610
Tom.

647
01:03:24,750 --> 01:03:27,950
Tom!

648
01:03:28,050 --> 01:03:31,380
- You scared me.
- I scared you?

649
01:03:32,510 --> 01:03:36,300
- What are you doing?
- I'm supposed to dig.

650
01:03:36,390 --> 01:03:39,090
- Whaddaya mean?
- I'm supposed to dig.

651
01:03:39,180 --> 01:03:41,250
Who says?

652
01:03:44,220 --> 01:03:47,150
I see. And what's Jake doing?

653
01:03:50,110 --> 01:03:52,860
Jake... is helping.

654
01:03:56,240 --> 01:03:59,240
- Why are you doing this?
- The water softens up the dirt.

655
01:03:59,330 --> 01:04:02,240
No. I mean...

656
01:04:02,330 --> 01:04:05,340
Could you just stop for a second?

657
01:04:05,420 --> 01:04:11,170
- Tom! Can you turn around and look at me?
- What... exactly don't you understand?

658
01:04:11,250 --> 01:04:13,410
I'm supposed to dig.

659
01:04:13,710 --> 01:04:16,840
- Why are you digging?
- I'm searching.

660
01:04:16,930 --> 01:04:20,010
- What are you searching for?
- The question is not what.

661
01:04:20,100 --> 01:04:23,590
We both know very well what,
even though we don't wanna admit it.

662
01:04:23,680 --> 01:04:30,430
The question, Maggie, which you can
plainly see I am very busy trying to answer...

663
01:04:30,520 --> 01:04:33,220
The question is where.

664
01:04:35,030 --> 01:04:37,110
Don't worry, he's OK.

665
01:04:37,620 --> 01:04:41,480
- It's not over there.
- We're calling the police.

666
01:04:42,330 --> 01:04:45,200
And tell them what, exactly?

667
01:04:45,540 --> 01:04:50,000
Practise it! Run it by me once.
I wanna see how it sounds out loud.

668
01:04:52,920 --> 01:04:55,000
Anything else?

669
01:04:57,850 --> 01:05:00,130
Tom, why don't you come inside with me?

670
01:05:00,220 --> 01:05:03,000
I wanna talk to you.
You're not yourself right now.

671
01:05:03,640 --> 01:05:06,010
This is just fucking typical!

672
01:05:06,110 --> 01:05:08,430
Now, what do you want me to do, Maggie?

673
01:05:08,860 --> 01:05:13,090
You want me to go inside and just...
sit down on the couch in front of the TV...

674
01:05:13,190 --> 01:05:19,120
..and drink beer until I fall asleep, and maybe
repeat the whole thing again tomorrow?

675
01:05:19,200 --> 01:05:21,600
- Be quiet!
- And the day after and the day after?

676
01:05:21,700 --> 01:05:24,530
- Just stop!
- Until...

677
01:05:24,620 --> 01:05:27,660
Until I grab my chest and die?

678
01:05:27,750 --> 01:05:32,160
I mean, this is the most important thing
that's ever happened to me.

679
01:05:32,250 --> 01:05:36,470
I mean, this is...
this is the most... important thing...

680
01:05:36,550 --> 01:05:40,680
..that I have ever done in my whole life,
in my whole stupid life!

681
01:05:40,760 --> 01:05:42,830
And you want me to just stop?

682
01:05:44,430 --> 01:05:47,050
No! No, I won't stop!

683
01:05:47,150 --> 01:05:49,550
I won't stop! I won't stop!

684
01:05:51,730 --> 01:05:54,430
Eight years, I've known you.

685
01:05:54,520 --> 01:05:58,520
Not once have you talked to me like this.
Not once.

686
01:05:58,610 --> 01:06:02,480
And if you do it again, I swear to God...

687
01:06:03,530 --> 01:06:09,320
And you know what? When you talk about
how ordinary you are and your stupid life...

688
01:06:09,420 --> 01:06:14,320
..you're saying ''Our stupid life,''
which I don't think is particularly stupid.

689
01:06:14,420 --> 01:06:18,250
So how the fuck
am I supposed to feel about that?

690
01:07:13,100 --> 01:07:15,470
Are you gonna drink that?

691
01:07:27,830 --> 01:07:29,540
I'm sorry.

692
01:07:31,870 --> 01:07:34,190
OK, I'm not sorry.

693
01:07:41,090 --> 01:07:43,700
- Who's that from?
- My brother Steve.

694
01:07:43,800 --> 01:07:47,630
- My grandma's going back in the hospital.
- No, she...

695
01:07:48,680 --> 01:07:50,140
What?

696
01:07:52,560 --> 01:07:54,100
What?

697
01:07:55,480 --> 01:07:57,190
Nothing.

698
01:08:07,120 --> 01:08:09,360
What is it?

699
01:08:17,090 --> 01:08:18,630
Hello?

700
01:08:18,710 --> 01:08:22,920
Oh, Steve. I'm sorry, we've been so busy.
I was just about...

701
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:25,090
What?

702
01:08:29,140 --> 01:08:31,670
She did?

703
01:08:32,560 --> 01:08:34,630
How am I doing, Dad?

704
01:08:34,720 --> 01:08:37,680
You're doing great, kid. You're doing great.

705
01:08:43,320 --> 01:08:45,810
I'm so sorry, baby.

706
01:08:48,580 --> 01:08:50,770
You knew.

707
01:08:50,870 --> 01:08:52,940
You knew, didn't you?

708
01:08:53,030 --> 01:08:55,570
When is the funeral?

709
01:08:55,670 --> 01:08:59,790
Sunday. We should leave as soon as we can.

710
01:09:02,040 --> 01:09:04,530
You want me to go with you?

711
01:09:06,180 --> 01:09:08,880
I just thought,
with your family and everything...

712
01:09:08,970 --> 01:09:12,920
Do I want you to go with me...
to my grandmother's funeral?

713
01:09:13,010 --> 01:09:16,140
She practically raised me!
Of course I want you to come.

714
01:09:16,230 --> 01:09:20,690
It's just, I'm kinda
in the middle of something here.

715
01:10:28,510 --> 01:10:32,120
$ 800 a month!
Can't get any fucking water!

716
01:10:32,220 --> 01:10:34,290
Fuck!

717
01:12:04,430 --> 01:12:06,400
Tools.

718
01:12:40,850 --> 01:12:42,640
Damn!

719
01:12:42,720 --> 01:12:44,790
Piece of shit!

720
01:13:39,120 --> 01:13:41,190
It's a rented house!

721
01:13:57,640 --> 01:13:59,460
- Hello?
- It's me.

722
01:13:59,550 --> 01:14:02,670
- Hey, baby, how're ya doin'?
- I'm OK.

723
01:14:02,760 --> 01:14:06,900
- How's your family?
- Drunk, fighting with each other.

724
01:14:06,980 --> 01:14:11,470
Listen, Maggie, I'm so sorry. I mean,
I should be there with ya. I'm an asshole.

725
01:14:11,560 --> 01:14:14,310
Yeah, well, you have your good points.

726
01:14:14,400 --> 01:14:18,270
- How do you feel?
- Fine. Fine. You know...

727
01:14:18,360 --> 01:14:22,230
Much... much... much better.
Everything's fine here. Really good.

728
01:14:22,320 --> 01:14:25,530
No...

729
01:14:26,330 --> 01:14:30,710
- No more digging?
- No. Back to normal.

730
01:14:30,790 --> 01:14:35,710
I'm sorry, too. I wish I hadn't stormed out.
I shouldn't have left you alone.

731
01:14:35,800 --> 01:14:37,960
I deserved it.

732
01:14:38,050 --> 01:14:41,870
Why don't you come up here with us?
You could make it in an hour.

733
01:14:41,970 --> 01:14:45,050
- Oh, no, I can't really do that.
- Why not?

734
01:14:45,130 --> 01:14:48,230
I'm not supposed to use the truck
for personal trips.

735
01:14:48,310 --> 01:14:53,980
- I'll pick you up. I'll leave right away.
- Oh, no, no, baby. Don't do that. That's crazy.

736
01:14:54,060 --> 01:14:55,980
- I gotta go.

737
01:14:56,070 --> 01:14:59,070
- I'll just pull up front and honk. Bye.
- No, no, no! No!

738
01:15:38,650 --> 01:15:40,850
OK, bub, you ready to go?

739
01:15:40,940 --> 01:15:44,060
I'm scared to go home.
I wanna stay at Uncle Steve's house.

740
01:15:44,150 --> 01:15:48,730
- Why are you scared?
- Because of the feathers.

741
01:15:49,040 --> 01:15:51,320
What feathers?

742
01:15:51,410 --> 01:15:54,110
I don't know. I just saw feathers.

743
01:15:55,920 --> 01:15:58,410
It's OK. I'll watch him.

744
01:15:58,510 --> 01:16:00,910
OK. You be good.

745
01:16:01,010 --> 01:16:03,290
Mom! Wait!

746
01:16:04,760 --> 01:16:07,050
You forgot this.

747
01:18:26,780 --> 01:18:29,060
Hi!

748
01:18:30,110 --> 01:18:31,820
Hi.

749
01:18:31,910 --> 01:18:34,440
Come here a sec.

750
01:18:34,530 --> 01:18:38,750
- What?
- Come closer. I can't hear you.

751
01:18:40,750 --> 01:18:44,790
- Are you talking to me?
- I wanna show you something.

752
01:18:44,870 --> 01:18:46,960
You wanna show me something?

753
01:18:47,050 --> 01:18:50,160
Well, yeah.
I don't see anybody else around.

754
01:18:51,220 --> 01:18:54,220
- What is it?
- It's a surprise.

755
01:18:54,300 --> 01:18:58,770
It's really great. Come on!
You won't believe it.

756
01:18:58,850 --> 01:19:01,090
Come on! It's freezing!

757
01:19:07,150 --> 01:19:09,230
Hey! Happy St Patrick's Day!

758
01:19:09,320 --> 01:19:12,150
- What's the surprise?
- Don't you have it?

759
01:19:12,240 --> 01:19:15,180
- Oh, yeah. The surprise?
- The surprise.

760
01:19:15,280 --> 01:19:17,820
- You need another drink.
- No, I got the spins.

761
01:19:17,910 --> 01:19:19,990
Drink, motherfucker, drink!

762
01:19:20,080 --> 01:19:24,150
- I don't think there is a surprise.
- Oh, yeah, there is. Yeah, there is.

763
01:19:24,250 --> 01:19:26,950
The surprise is we decided
we wanna be your friends.

764
01:19:27,050 --> 01:19:28,790
- You do?
- Yeah.

765
01:19:28,880 --> 01:19:33,450
- Why do you wanna be my friends now?
- Are you kidding? Look at yourself.

766
01:19:35,510 --> 01:19:38,090
Look.

767
01:19:38,180 --> 01:19:40,930
You can take your coat off, you know.

768
01:19:41,640 --> 01:19:44,390
- You want a drink?
- I'm not supposed to.

769
01:19:44,480 --> 01:19:48,560
Don't you do anything
you're not supposed to?

770
01:19:48,650 --> 01:19:50,930
I do.

771
01:19:52,860 --> 01:19:54,320
Yeah.

772
01:19:54,400 --> 01:19:56,900
Momma, you are hot!

773
01:19:57,000 --> 01:20:00,280
Come on, let's be friends, huh?

774
01:20:00,370 --> 01:20:02,650
Well...

775
01:20:02,750 --> 01:20:05,500
..you can kiss me if you want to.

776
01:20:05,580 --> 01:20:08,080
Yeah... Yeah.

777
01:20:16,600 --> 01:20:20,090
- Not... not like that, OK?
- OK. OK. OK...

778
01:20:29,780 --> 01:20:34,470
- I wanna go home.
- Not now, no, no. Come on...

779
01:20:34,570 --> 01:20:36,650
- I'll be your friend.
- I want to, but...

780
01:20:36,740 --> 01:20:40,570
Just be nice to me, huh? Be a good girl.
You are a good girl, aren't you?

781
01:20:40,660 --> 01:20:43,610
- I have to go home.
- How about a helmet wash?

782
01:20:43,700 --> 01:20:46,490
I have to go home.
I have to go home!

783
01:20:56,260 --> 01:20:58,670
No! Stop!

784
01:21:00,680 --> 01:21:03,250
Shut up! Shut up!

785
01:21:03,350 --> 01:21:05,420
Shut... God!

786
01:21:05,510 --> 01:21:08,640
Shut up!

787
01:21:10,270 --> 01:21:13,110
Make her stop, man!
Make her stop screaming!

788
01:21:13,190 --> 01:21:14,600
Shut her up, man!

789
01:21:18,580 --> 01:21:21,240
Use your jacket or something!
Put it over her face!

790
01:21:22,450 --> 01:21:23,910
Shut up!

791
01:21:47,270 --> 01:21:49,800
Oh, my God!

792
01:21:50,860 --> 01:21:52,930
What the fuck did you do that for?

793
01:21:53,020 --> 01:21:55,090
- Is she dead?
- No shit, she's dead!

794
01:21:55,190 --> 01:21:57,690
Oh, my God!

795
01:21:57,780 --> 01:22:01,030
- Look at her tongue, man.
- I am not here.

796
01:22:01,120 --> 01:22:03,560
I've never seen nobody dead before.

797
01:22:03,660 --> 01:22:06,280
- I can't be here.
- It's fucking gross.

798
01:22:06,380 --> 01:22:08,910
This isn't happening.

799
01:22:09,000 --> 01:22:13,240
Fucking plastic over her face!
Good thinking, Adam

800
01:22:14,290 --> 01:22:17,140
Well, what do we do now?

801
01:22:52,460 --> 01:22:54,990
How's he doin'?

802
01:22:55,080 --> 01:22:58,710
He might make it. He might not.

803
01:22:59,760 --> 01:23:03,750
Sheila's over at the hospital.
I'm gonna head over.

804
01:23:03,840 --> 01:23:06,170
Frank... I'm sorry.

805
01:23:07,230 --> 01:23:12,840
I'm sorry because...
I think I know why Adam shot himself.

806
01:23:13,440 --> 01:23:16,850
And... I gotta call the police about it.

807
01:23:17,990 --> 01:23:20,650
And I don't want you
to hear it from them.

808
01:23:20,740 --> 01:23:24,070
And I don't want Sheila
to read about it in the paper.

809
01:23:24,150 --> 01:23:28,540
I think you have a right to know
before anybody else.

810
01:23:28,620 --> 01:23:30,860
What are you talking about, Tom?

811
01:23:33,710 --> 01:23:36,200
Come with me.

812
01:23:36,300 --> 01:23:39,000
Wait here for a second.

813
01:23:46,310 --> 01:23:49,230
It better be important.

814
01:24:00,610 --> 01:24:03,220
Come on!
Come on, come on, come on, come on!

815
01:24:06,290 --> 01:24:08,530
How the hell did you find this?

816
01:24:09,120 --> 01:24:11,570
Does it matter?

817
01:24:12,620 --> 01:24:15,230
Well, you don't know
if it was Kurt and Adam.

818
01:24:16,210 --> 01:24:18,120
Yeah, I do.

819
01:24:19,550 --> 01:24:22,080
But you don't have anything to...

820
01:24:23,130 --> 01:24:28,720
Tom, you're talking like a goddamn lunatic!
That's what people are gonna say.

821
01:24:28,810 --> 01:24:31,720
It's just a body.
It doesn't prove anything.

822
01:24:32,520 --> 01:24:34,060
She's...

823
01:24:34,140 --> 01:24:37,350
She's got somebody's hair in her hand.

824
01:24:38,400 --> 01:24:41,510
They're gonna be able
to tell whose it is.

825
01:24:45,280 --> 01:24:47,650
Hey, Frank.

826
01:24:50,240 --> 01:24:53,080
We... we gotta call the cops.

827
01:24:55,330 --> 01:24:58,700
What were we supposed to do?

828
01:24:59,210 --> 01:25:01,830
It was an accident.

829
01:25:03,880 --> 01:25:07,460
The kids come to us,
she's already dead.

830
01:25:08,720 --> 01:25:13,350
The damage is done. There's nothing
anybody can do to bring her back.

831
01:25:14,810 --> 01:25:19,680
But these kids got...
everything ahead of them.

832
01:25:20,980 --> 01:25:23,850
So what were we supposed to do, Tom?

833
01:25:23,940 --> 01:25:28,270
Send our sons to jail for the rest of their lives
because of her?

834
01:25:29,330 --> 01:25:31,770
Who are you planning
to shoot with that?

835
01:25:33,330 --> 01:25:37,320
- Get the hell outta here, Tom.
- Hey, Frank... come on upstairs.

836
01:25:37,420 --> 01:25:39,450
We... we could talk about this.

837
01:25:39,540 --> 01:25:42,910
I've been living with this for...
six months.

838
01:25:46,220 --> 01:25:49,140
Six fucking months!

839
01:25:50,890 --> 01:25:56,260
Do you think anything you have to say is
gonna make one bit of difference to me?

840
01:25:57,360 --> 01:26:00,520
- Get the hell outta here!
- I'm not leaving until...

841
01:26:00,610 --> 01:26:01,760
Get out!

842
01:26:02,900 --> 01:26:05,140
Get out!

843
01:26:16,120 --> 01:26:19,910
- Hi.
- Hi. Hi.

844
01:26:20,210 --> 01:26:24,990
- Well, it's really pouring, huh?
- Yeah, looks like it.

845
01:26:25,540 --> 01:26:28,800
You got a minute?

846
01:26:28,890 --> 01:26:31,460
No, I'm... kinda busy right now.

847
01:26:31,550 --> 01:26:33,540
It's important.

848
01:26:38,690 --> 01:26:42,380
I don't really
have time to talk right now, Harry.

849
01:26:42,480 --> 01:26:45,180
Jesus! This rain, huh?

850
01:26:46,060 --> 01:26:50,280
Harry, like I said, you know,
I'm really kind of busy right now.

851
01:26:50,360 --> 01:26:53,700
Kurt, I know you weren't raised in a barn.
Close that door.

852
01:26:53,780 --> 01:26:56,460
Maybe I could call you later
or something?

853
01:26:59,750 --> 01:27:02,360
Tom, we got ourselves
a serious problem here.

854
01:27:02,460 --> 01:27:05,570
Whaddaya mean?

855
01:27:05,670 --> 01:27:08,370
What the hell you think
you're doing to my house?

856
01:27:08,880 --> 01:27:12,050
I heard all this pounding going on.
I thought I'd check it out.

857
01:27:12,130 --> 01:27:14,750
I didn't think you'd be
wrecking the place!

858
01:27:15,300 --> 01:27:17,840
What's the matter with you?

859
01:27:17,940 --> 01:27:21,590
Oh, don't worry. I'm gonna...
I'm gonna take care of that.

860
01:27:21,690 --> 01:27:25,260
I was trying to fix your water main,
you know - it was leaking...

861
01:27:25,350 --> 01:27:28,530
..and I couldn't get to it
from underneath the house.

862
01:27:29,860 --> 01:27:34,730
I mean... I couldn't
get under the house to get to it.

863
01:27:35,860 --> 01:27:38,440
Is that right?

864
01:27:39,540 --> 01:27:42,290
Damn. A lotta water damage?

865
01:27:43,040 --> 01:27:45,650
Some.

866
01:27:45,750 --> 01:27:48,040
Can I look around?

867
01:27:49,550 --> 01:27:53,500
Yeah. Yeah, sure. Sure.
Help yourself.

868
01:27:55,170 --> 01:27:57,510
Maybe you'd better show me
where it's at.

869
01:28:00,230 --> 01:28:04,170
Well, you guys'll be able to see.
I gotta take off right now.

870
01:28:06,490 --> 01:28:09,570
I'm almost afraid to look.

871
01:28:09,650 --> 01:28:11,390
- Drink it.
- Right.

872
01:28:11,490 --> 01:28:13,890
Hurry up.

873
01:28:15,150 --> 01:28:18,360
The water main doesn't run
under the house.

874
01:28:21,500 --> 01:28:23,690
Well, I know that now.

875
01:28:25,330 --> 01:28:28,670
Shit, Tom.

876
01:28:38,810 --> 01:28:41,670
Get him on the rug.

877
01:28:47,230 --> 01:28:49,720
- Don't look at him. Roll him over.
- Yeah.

878
01:28:49,820 --> 01:28:52,510
Let's go! All right...

879
01:28:52,610 --> 01:28:54,890
..get outta the way.

880
01:30:35,460 --> 01:30:37,540
Tom?

881
01:30:42,050 --> 01:30:44,580
Are you here?

882
01:30:51,350 --> 01:30:53,430
Shit!

883
01:30:59,320 --> 01:31:02,270
Out of the way, Kurt!

884
01:31:26,090 --> 01:31:30,840
They were gonna kill you, Tommy.
You and Maggie both.

885
01:31:36,950 --> 01:31:40,480
- Are you OK?
- Yeah.

886
01:31:52,620 --> 01:31:55,400
Cold-blooded murder.

887
01:31:56,880 --> 01:31:59,830
I can't let something like that happen.

888
01:32:00,880 --> 01:32:03,250
Not here.

889
01:32:04,300 --> 01:32:07,390
This was a decent neighbourhood.

890
01:34:03,130 --> 01:34:05,200
Jake...

891
01:34:06,340 --> 01:34:08,420
Jake...

892
01:34:12,510 --> 01:34:14,470
Jake...

